-- Russia’s Sown Crops Affected by ’Abnormal’ Heat, Interfax Says
-- B y   Y u l i y a   F e d o r i n o v a
-- 2012-07-27T10:13:06Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-27/russia-s-sown-crops-affected-by-abnormal-heat-interfax-says.html
Russia  has 4.4 million hectares
(10.9 million acres) of sown crops which have been affected by
“abnormal” heat,  Interfax  reported, citing Igor Manylov,
deputy agriculture minister.  That represents about 6 percent of the total crop land,
according to the newswire.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Yuliya Fedorinova in Moscow at 
